I heard it all when I first started my business… “Be careful” “No one actually makes money” “The trips & car aren’t real” “The products won’t work” and the list could go on 

All I knew at that time was…
I had just put my two weeks in at my job where I was extremely under appreciated. I had no income coming in, I was in college with no idea what I wanted to do after school. My parents were putting myself and my older sister through college & our living expenses. They paid for all of our cars and my little sister was about to head to college too. I didn’t know about the car program before but once I found out about it, I knew I wanted to take a car payment off my parents. I had hair extensions for over 7 years before trying Monat. I tried everything on the market and nothing worked. My hair wouldn’t grow and it was beyond damaged. 

Within 9 months of starting my business, I felt loved and appreciated in this business. I found a passion and love for helping others achieve their goals and go for more in life. I took my extensions out within 2 months of using the products. I was able to take trips without wondering where the money was coming from. I picked up my first Cadillac and took a car payment off my parents 🙌 I earned a free trip to the Bahamas and took Brady with me! My income was the highest it had ever been and kept growing. 

Moral of the story, people are gonna tell you not to do something but that’s okay if it’s not THEIR dream. But if there’s something weighing on your heart… chase it!! I promise you it’s worth investing in. I can’t imagine where I would be if I let peoples thoughts and opinions and get in the way of me trying something that completely changed my life.

This was hands down the hardest challenge I’ve ever set for myself. Towards the end is where I really felt the gap start to close in with how many miles I had left and the window to midnight kept getting closer. Sunday night I got on my bike at 5:30 PM and got off to get food about 15-20 min and then was on until 11:15 pm. I spent almost 3 hours out of the saddle, resistance over 55 with my speed over 20 MPH to get to the finish line. 

I knew this goal was happening, there was never a thought of quitting… as I always tell @those.young.ones once I set my goal there’s no backing down but I can’t change it. I wanted to be able to give it everything and work as hard as possible for our team. 

When I finished my last group ride, I had 2.9 miles to go, I started a just ride and jammed out to 3 of my favorite Taylor Swift songs, sprinting through the finish line to Cruel Summer & I wouldn’t have changed that moment for anything. 

In that moment I felt…
POWERFUL, PROUD, SUPPORTED, LOVED, STRONG & DETERMINED 🥹
